parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings, which can result in running out of fuel, stalling, or other safety issues.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads empty when the tank is full
or shows a half tank when empty
the fuel gauge does not reset until the tank is filled and driven for a certain distance
the check engine light is on
and the service engine soon light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
hesitates
or loses power
the transmission shifts harshly
the vehicle vibrates
and the check engine light is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle overheats
the coolant leaks
and the radiator hoses are soaked in transmission fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure Due to Radiator Coolant Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will not accelerate
the transmission will not shift gears
the check engine light is on
the vehicle will stall
the transmission fluid and coolant will mix
and the radiator will leak coolant into the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leakage of radiator coolant into the transmission can cause the transmission to fail, leading to sudden loss of power, stalling, or difficulty shifting gears, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as vibration
shaking
or jerking when shifting gears
unusual noises
or difficulty accelerating. The coolant and transmission fluid may mix
causing damage to the transmission and radiator.
